CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779318188
OL,3,CFormer Cuban president Raul Castro
OL,4,Ccharged in US over 1996 downing of two
OL,5,Cplanes
OL,7,FBut those calls went unheeded, and on
OL,8,FFebruary 24, 1996, missiles fired by
OL,9,FRussian-made MiG-29 fighter jets
OL,10,Fdowned two unarmed civilian Cessna
OL,11,Fplanes a short distance north of
OL,12,FHavana just beyond Cuba's airspace.
OL,13,FAll four men aboard were killed.
OL,26,@kD@Zrz
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30515
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779318188
OL,3,CFormer Cuban president Raul Castro
OL,4,Ccharged in US over 1996 downing of two
OL,5,Cplanes
OL,7,FIn the end, the Clinton administration
OL,8,Findicted four individuals, including
OL,9,Fthe MiG pilots, the head of the Cuban
OL,10,Fair force and the head of a Cuban spy
OL,11,Fnetwork in Miami ` the only one to see
OL,12,Fthe inside of a US prison ` for
OL,13,Fproviding valuable intelligence about
OL,14,Fthe flights.
OL,16,FThe incident led the US to harden its
OL,17,Fposition against Cuba, even though the
OL,18,FCold War had ended and the Castros'
OL,19,Fsupport for revolution across Latin
OL,20,FAmerica was a fading memory.
OL,26,@kD@Zrz
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30516
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779318188
OL,3,CFormer Cuban president Raul Castro
OL,4,Ccharged in US over 1996 downing of two
OL,5,Cplanes
OL,7,FBut Castro himself was spared as the
OL,8,FClinton administration, which had
OL,9,Fquietly sought to expand relations
OL,10,Fwith Cuba prior to the incident,
OL,11,Fraised foreign policy concerns about
OL,12,Fsuch a high-profile indictment.
OL,14,F"Raul was definitely one who slipped
OL,15,Fthrough the noose," said former
OL,16,Ffederal prosecutor Guy Lewis. "The
OL,17,Fcrime is notorious.
OL,26,@kD@ZrzvD@AOUvD@DrzwD@SO]xD@_OU
